EXTRACTED VALUE: What would've otherwise been a fun multiplayer shooter is marred by a series of technical issues.
It may have few aspirations beyond being a dumb FPS, but it never fails to make the most of its limited talents. [Christmas 2007, p.97]
The game is merely frustrating until you get to Havana, when it becomes a nightmare of trial-and-error repetition.
For balls to the wall, mindless shooting this game will satisfy, if you can focus on the destruction you cause and not the technical short comings.
